## Generated Output Shape

For a `User` model with `id Int @id`, `email String`, `name String?`, the generator outputs `client.ts`:

```typescript
// Generated by @prisma/client-generator-rest-api — do not edit manually.

export interface User {
  id: number
  email: string
  name: string | null
}

class UserResource {
  readonly #baseUrl: string
  readonly #headers: Record<string, string>
  // ... findMany, findUnique, create, update, delete, #request
}

export interface RestApiClientOptions { baseUrl: string; headers?: Record<string, string> }
export class RestApiClient {
  readonly user: UserResource
  constructor(options: RestApiClientOptions) { ... }
}
```

HTTP conventions used:
| Method     | HTTP           | Path            |
|------------|----------------|-----------------|
| findMany   | GET            | `/users?...`    |
| findUnique | GET            | `/users/:id`    |
| create     | POST           | `/users`        |
| update     | PUT            | `/users/:id`    |
| delete     | DELETE         | `/users/:id`    |

